(34, 1, 'Admin Catalog Import Export Fields', '<div class=\"grouplisting\">                            \r\n	<div class=\"groups group-js\">                                \r\n		<div class=\"group__head group__head-js\">\r\n			<h5> Product Catalog Content </h5></div>                                \r\n		<div class=\"group__body group__body-js\">                                    \r\n			<h5>Product Identifier</h5>                                    \r\n			<p>User defined unique identifier for the Product. This works as a unique key for the system to identify a particular Product.</p>                                    \r\n			<h5>Username</h5>                                    \r\n			<p>For admin this field needs to be left blank. In case an option is added by a seller then seller username will be displayed in this field.  </p>                                    \r\n			<h5>Name</h5>                                    \r\n			<p>User defined field for product name.</p>                                    \r\n			<h5>Description</h5>                                    \r\n			<p>User defined field for product description. </p>                                    \r\n			<h5>Youtube video</h5>                                    \r\n			<p>User defined field for product Youtube video URL</p>                                    \r\n			<h5>Category Identifier</h5>                                    \r\n			<p> User defined unique identifier for the category. This field needs to be the same as Category Identifier defined in Categories Content sheet.  </p>                                    \r\n			<h5>Brand Identifier</h5>                                    \r\n			<p>User defined unique identifier for the Brand. This field needs to be the same as Brand Identifier defined in Brand Content sheet.  </p>                                    \r\n			<h5>Product Type Identifier</h5>                                    \r\n			<p>User defined input field to denote the type of the Product. Possible inputs for this field are \'Physical\' and \'Digital\'. </p>                                    \r\n			<h5>Model</h5>                                    \r\n			<p>User defined field for product model.</p>                                    \r\n			<h5>Minimum selling price</h5>                                    \r\n			<p>User defined field for minimum selling price for the product.</p>                                    \r\n			<h5>Tax Category Identifier</h5>                                    \r\n			<p>User defined unique identifier for the Tax category. This field needs to be the same as Tax Category Identifier defined in the Admin console under the Sales Tax option page.</p>                                    \r\n			<h5>Length</h5>                                    \r\n			<p>User defined field for product package length.</p>                                    \r\n			<h5>Width</h5>                                    \r\n			<p>User defined field for product package width.</p>                                    \r\n                                    \r\n			<h5>Height</h5>                                    \r\n			<p>User defined field for product package Height.</p>                                    \r\n                                    \r\n			<h5>Dimension Unit Identifier</h5>                                    \r\n			<p>User defined input field to denote the unit of the dimensions of the package. Possible inputs for this field are \'Inch\', \'Centimeter\' and \'Feet\'. </p>                                    \r\n                                    \r\n			<h5>Weight </h5>                                    \r\n			<p>User defined field for product package Weight.</p>                                    \r\n			<h5>Weight Unit Identifier</h5>                                    \r\n			<p>User defined input field to denote the unit of the weight of the package. . Possible inputs for this field are \'Gram\', \'Kilogram\' and \'Pound\'.</p>                                    \r\n			<h5>Ean/upc Code</h5>                                    \r\n			<p>User defined field for EAN/UPC code of the product.</p>                                    \r\n			<h5>Shipping country Code</h5>                                    \r\n			<p>This field needs to be the same as country code defined in Countries Content sheet.  </p>                                    \r\n			<h5>Added On</h5>                                    \r\n			<p>User defined field for product add date to the system.</p>                                    \r\n			<h5>Free Shipping</h5>                                    \r\n			<p>User defined field to mark a particular Product is available for free shipping. Possible inputs for this field are Yes and No.</p>                                    \r\n			<h5>COD Available</h5>                                    \r\n			<p>User defined field to mark a particular Product is available for Cash on Delivery or not. Possible inputs for this field are Yes and No.</p>                                    \r\n			<h5>Featured</h5>                                    \r\n			<p>User defined field to mark a particular Product as featured or not. Possible inputs for this field are Yes and No. </p>                                    \r\n			<h5>Approved</h5>                                    \r\n			<p>User defined field to mark a particular Product as Approved or not. Possible inputs for this field are Yes and No. Default value should be set as \'Yes\' to display products in the system.</p>                                    \r\n			<h5>Active</h5>                                    \r\n			<p>User defined field to mark a particular Product as active in the system or not. Possible inputs for this field are Yes and No. Default value should be set as \'Yes\'. </p>                                    \r\n			<h5>Deleted</h5>                                    \r\n			<p>User defined field to mark a particular product as deleted in the system or not. Possible inputs for this field are Yes and No. Default value should be set as \'No\' to display products in the system. </p>                                </div>                            </div>                            \r\n	<div class=\"groups group-js\">                                \r\n		<div class=\"group__head group__head-js\">\r\n			<h5> Product Option Content </h5></div>                                \r\n		<div class=\"group__body group__body-js\">                                    \r\n			<ul>                                    \r\n                                        \r\n				<li>                                        \r\n                                            \r\n					<h5>Product Identifier</h5>                                        \r\n                                            \r\n					<p>User defined unique identifier for the Product. This field needs to be the same as Product Identifier defined in the Product Catalog Content sheet. </p>                                    </li>                                    \r\n                                        \r\n				<li>                                        \r\n                                            \r\n					<h5>Option Identifier</h5>                                        \r\n                                            \r\n					<p>User defined unique identifier for the Option. This field needs to be the same as Option Identifier defined in Option Content sheet. </p>                                        </li>                                \r\n                                    \r\n			</ul>                                </div>                            </div>                            \r\n	<div class=\"groups group-js\">                                \r\n		<div class=\"group__head group__head-js\">\r\n			<h5> Product Tag Content</h5></div>                                \r\n		<div class=\"group__body group__body-js\">                                    \r\n			<ul>                                    \r\n                                        \r\n				<li>                                        \r\n                                            \r\n					<h5>Product Identifier</h5>                                        \r\n                                            \r\n					<p>User defined unique identifier for the Product. This field needs to be the same as Product Identifier defined in the Product Catalog Content sheet.</p>                                    </li>                                    \r\n                                        \r\n				<li>                                        \r\n                                            \r\n					<h5>Tag Identifier</h5>                                        \r\n                                            \r\n					<p>User defined unique identifier for the Tag. This field needs to be the same as Tag Identifier defined in Tag Content sheet. </p>                                    </li>                                \r\n                                    \r\n			</ul>                                </div>                            </div>                            \r\n	<div class=\"groups group-js\">                                \r\n		<div class=\"group__head group__head-js\">\r\n			<h5> Product Specification Content </h5></div>                                \r\n		<div class=\"group__body group__body-js\">                                    \r\n			<ul>                                    \r\n                                        \r\n				<li>                                        \r\n                                            \r\n					<h5>Product Identifier</h5>                                        \r\n                                            \r\n					<p>User defined unique identifier for the Product. This field needs to be the same as Product Identifier defined in the Product Catalog Content sheet.    </p>                                    </li>                                    \r\n                                        \r\n				<li>                                        \r\n                                            \r\n					<h5>Lang Code</h5>                                        \r\n                                            \r\n					<p>User defined field to link the product specification for a particular language. Language codes can be looked up by clicking the language option in the top header. </p>                                    </li>                                    \r\n                                        \r\n				<li>                                        \r\n                                            \r\n					<h5>Specification Name</h5>                                        \r\n                                            \r\n					<p>User defined field for product specification name.</p>                                    </li>                                    \r\n                                        \r\n				<li>                                        \r\n                                            \r\n					<h5>Specification Value</h5>                                        \r\n                                            \r\n					<p>User defined field for product specification Value.</p>                                    </li>                                \r\n                                    \r\n			</ul>                                </div>                            </div>                            \r\n	<div class=\"groups group-js\">                                \r\n		<div class=\"group__head group__head-js\">\r\n			<h5> Product Shipping Content </h5></div>                                \r\n		<div class=\"group__body group__body-js\">                                    \r\n			<ul>                                    \r\n                                    \r\n				<li>                                        \r\n                                        \r\n					<h5>Product Identifier</h5>                                        \r\n                                        \r\n					<p>User defined unique identifier for the Product. This field needs to be the same as Product Identifier defined in the Product Catalog Content sheet.</p>                                    </li>                                    \r\n                                    \r\n				<li>                                        \r\n                                        \r\n					<h5>Username</h5>                                        \r\n                                        \r\n					<p>For admin this field needs to be left blank. In case an option is added by a seller then seller username will be displayed in this field. </p>                                    </li>                                    \r\n                                    \r\n				<li>                                        \r\n                                        \r\n					<h5>Shipping Country Code</h5>                                        \r\n                                        \r\n					<p>This field needs to be the same as country code defined in Countries Content sheet. This field can be left blank if the product has no restrictions on the countries it is shipped to.</p>                                    </li>                                    \r\n                                    \r\n				<li>                                        \r\n                                        \r\n					<h5>Shipping Company Identifier</h5>                                        \r\n                                        \r\n					<p>User defined unique identifier for the Shipping company identifier. This field needs to be the same as the Shipping Company Identifier defined in the Admin console>Shipping API>Shipping Companies page.  </p>                                        </li>                                    \r\n                                    \r\n				<li>                                        \r\n                                        \r\n					<h5>Shipping Duration Identifier</h5>                                        \r\n                                        \r\n					<p>User defined unique identifier for the Shipping Duration identifier. This field needs to be the same as the Shipping Duration Identifier defined in the Admin console>Shipping API>Duration Labels page. </p>                                    </li>                                    \r\n                                    \r\n				<li>                                        \r\n                                        \r\n					<h5>Cost</h5>                                        \r\n                                        \r\n					<p>User defined field for product shipping cost.</p>                                    </li>                                    \r\n                                    \r\n				<li>                                        \r\n                                        \r\n					<h5>Additional Item Cost</h5>                                        \r\n                                        \r\n					<p>User defined field for additional shipping cost per product.</p>                                    </li>                                \r\n                                \r\n			</ul>                                </div>                            </div>                            \r\n	<div class=\"groups group-js\">                                \r\n		<div class=\"group__head group__head-js\">\r\n			<h5> Product Catalog Media  </h5></div>                                \r\n		<div class=\"group__body group__body-js\">                                    \r\n			<ul>                                    \r\n                                    \r\n				<li>                                        \r\n                                        \r\n					<h5>Product Identifier</h5>                                        \r\n                                        \r\n					<p>User defined unique identifier for the Product. This field needs to be the same as Product Identifier defined in the Product Catalog Content sheet. </p>                                    </li>                                    \r\n                                    \r\n				<li>                                        \r\n                                        \r\n					<h5>Lang Code</h5>                                        \r\n                                        \r\n					<p>User defined field to link the product image for a particular language. \'Universal\' is to be used as an option to link the media in all languages. Language codes can be looked up by clicking the language option in the top header. Language codes need to be used if the Product has different images for each language.</p>                                    </li>                                    \r\n                                    \r\n				<li>                                        \r\n                                        \r\n					<h5>Option Identifier</h5>                                        \r\n                                        \r\n					<p>User defined unique identifier for the option. This field value needs to be the same as the Option Identifier defined in Options Content sheet.   </p>                                    </li>                                    \r\n                                    \r\n				<li>                                        \r\n                                        \r\n					<h5>Option value Identifier</h5>                                        \r\n                                        \r\n					<p>User defined unique identifier for the option value. This field value needs to be the same as the Option value Identifier defined in Options Value Content sheet. </p>                                    </li>                                    \r\n                                    \r\n				<li>                                        \r\n                                        \r\n					<h5>File Path</h5>                                        \r\n                                        \r\n					<p>File path needs to be a publically accessible URL for example URL\'s from Google Drive, Dropbox etc. Images stored locally on your personal device/machine cannot be uploaded. Preferred image dimensions for the product images are greater than 500*500 pixels. </p>                                    </li>                                    \r\n                                    \r\n				<li>                                        \r\n                                        \r\n					<h5>File Name</h5>                                        \r\n                                        \r\n					<p>Name of the image file. </p>                                    </li>                                    \r\n                                    \r\n				<li>                                        \r\n                                        \r\n					<h5>Display order</h5>                                        \r\n                                        \r\n					<p>When a product has multiple images then this field defines the order of display. If you are unsure about this field add display order as \'1\'. </p>                                    </li>                                \r\n                                \r\n			</ul>                                </div>                            </div>                        </div>'),
